Subject: Re: [sfraves] NRR:  Spam does pay off (I think)


 In email, as in snailmail and those photocopied advertisments
posted on laundromat bulletin boards, do not pay money to get leads
on making money. The usual result is you will get information that
you could have found out all by yourself. Or else you'll get a list
of real but crappy jobs.

 As far as conducting surveys from home for $$:

 Go to http://directory.google.com/

 Search for the words [ "work at home" surveys ]

 Disclaimer - I've never tried any "work at home" offers, so I don't
have any information about any of the businesses in the search results.

 Good luck Osby!

 - Larry Ching

Subject: RE: [sfraves] two year olds don't need spankings NRR

You know, I wasn't going to respond to this thread on general
principles, especially since this brings out SUCH inflammatory emotions
in some people...  And the actions of the parents in this example
weren't strictly defined.

But I tend to agree with siphon, I think that when you are not a parent,
and you are in public that you really should give the benefit of the
doubt to the parent... Of COURSE when an infant shows OBVIOUS signs of
abuse then something really should be said.

Many children are not receptive to "voice commands" (they aren't
animals, My dog doesn't always respond to my commands, and I VERY RARELY
discipline him with anything NEAR forceful physical contact), many
children will take the opportunity to misbehave in unusual ways when
they are in public.  I have always felt that a certain amount of respect
is due elders, and strangers, and while I only ever felt my fathers hand
once in my life I think that it is not entirely unacceptable to enforce
your rules through the use of SOME physical force...

Now I cannot give these parameters, and it would be extremely difficult
to tell another parent what they SHOULD be...  Every parent needs to
shoulder the responsibility of defining them individually, and needs to
have the respect of society that they deserve as guardians.

(that said: people who abuse children are sick, they NEED the attention
of authorities, and society in general)

Jodiah

Subject: [sfraves] [bsp] LAST HALFLIFE AT AN SIBIN - TONIGHT - FREE!

hey all,
for those of you not in the know, the an sibin dj bar has been sold to new
owners, and due to their possible choice to disband several of the existing
nights, halflife chose to move to a new venue. thus, tonight will be the
last halflife on a monday night at an sibin, so please come by, give brooke
a hug, have a drink, and pay your respects to this long-lived dnb night.

myself and djsnm will be opening the night (as usual) from 9-10:30 with some
breaks infused mash-up goodness, and after that jest1 and his 510 and
halflife resedent lackeys take over.

remember, it's free. no excuse!

they say in England, "He's fuckin 'avin it!"

him recognition across the globe. Ant plays throughout the US, Canada, =
South Africa, Venezuela & Japan.=20

Quotes for the end of the Year: 2002

The spirit of Plato dies hard.  We have been unable to escape the
philosophical tradition that what we can see and measure in the world is
merely the superficial and imperfect representation of an underlying
reality.
                -- S.J. Gould, "The Mismeasure of Man"


As long as war is regarded as wicked, it will always have its fascination.
When it is looked upon as vulgar, it will cease to be popular.
                -- Oscar Wilde, "Intentions"


"Pay no attention to the man behind the curtain."
-- The Wizard Of Oz

Regards,

Karina

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Resolution **

Resolution presented by After Party Productions.  2am-Noon;  Don't want
the night to end at 2am? Drive on over to the first party of 2003. Planet
New Year Massive After Party!  DJs Spinning Their Way Into the New Year:
STAGE ONE: Joey Mazzola vs Jay Walker; Dyloot , Reckless Ryan, Felipe
Avelar vs Frequency, Valerie Sparks vs Matt Frost Dj Elz vs Deckster,
Spective, RxFX (Jimmy B. + Ricky Parsons), Kid Cosmo, Akil Taylor,
Absolute Alex, Dj Bjorn, OrionZ ; STAGE TWO: Denise, Tronic, Frank Nitty,
James Dub, Bazooka Joe, J Marr, The Doctor, Carlos Alfonzo, Cise1, DJ
Orbit, Dough Boy vs Kid Matt ; Close Virgin East Bay Venue that holds 2000
party people! PLEASE Respect the venue so we can use it again!

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D360
East Bay Area California, USA

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Weekly: Progress **

Without deviation from the norm, Progress is not possible. Well, the time
has come to deviate! Featuring the most talented DJ's, and Remix artist's
SF has to offer showcasing their own eclectic taste in dance music. From
booty-shaking progressive house and a touch of breaks-n-trance. Let the
music guide you through your evening - accompanied by those TOKYO Tea's!
Resident weekly DJs include Joseph Lee, Ollie Vaughn, Yoda, and Todd
Prophet. Plus weekly headliners including Mystre, Jerry Bonham, Tracy,
Charlotte the Baroness, Kramer, and many more! admission: cover TBA, 21+
Located @ The Galaxy Club, 1840 Haight St. (between Stanyan & Cole), San
Francisco. Upper Haight. phone: 415.387.2996 booking line: 415.387.2998
fax: 415.876.3741 e-mail: galaxyclub@pacbell.net bar hours: Daily (12 noon
- 2 am)

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D296 San
Francisco California, USA

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** New Year's Eve Countdown **

New Year's Eve Countdown presented by DMZ Ent, Spillo, Raff Ent.  For
yesterday is but a dream and tomorrow is a New Year. Join us in welcoming
the New Year at Countdown 2002 to 2003&#65533;. Welcome the New Year with
the best DJs, incredible multi-colored light and laser show, earthshaking
sound, delicious hot & cold food, full bar and our eclectic collection of
European and Eastern sounds. Event is for all ages. Dress code enforced.
Dinner Session begins at 5:00pm, Party Begins at 9:30. We have 4 different
prices and ways for you to get inside and have fun on New Year's Eve. Ask
dinner reservation officer for an explanation.

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D361 SF Bay
Area California, USA

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Weekly: Robotic **

Ultra Hour directly followed by Robotic featuring Resident DJ's: Mateo
Jones, Seese, Rachel, Gabe, Ben, Drew + special guests. Starting @ 6PM
with a downtempo/deep house happy hour (cheap drinks till 8!), getting
funkier as the night progresses and going strong untill 2AM. With a newly
remodeled dance floor, trippy anime videos, multiple Playstation 2's, and
a great atmosphere...come check out the new look!  Located @ POW! (corner
of 6th & Mission), San Francisco.

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D394 San
Francisco California, USA

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Backflip NYE 2003 **

Sebastien and Tony Kutulas present...New Years Eve 2003 Backflip NYE 2003
- Come celebrate New Years Eve at our indoor outdoor extravaganza with San
Francisco's finest house, funky house, and hip-hop DJs in three different
areas & an unforgettable visual experience. This unique event will only
happen once in a lifetime being that it is Backflip's closing night as
well as New Years Eve.

Featuring house DJs Didje Kelli, Dimitrius Mykonos, Re Pete, Raoul Kahn,
Almir, and BB Hayes. Featuring hip-hop DJs Big Bad Bruce, Danny Brown, and
Sol.* go-go dancers * visuals * lounges * vip areas & private booths * SF
restaurants * party favors * multiple bars * champagne bar * heated and
tented outdoor areas * smoking outdoors * phoenix hotel room packages
available 415.776.1380 Tickets $30 pre-sale-ends December 13th; $40
dollars after. Buy online at groovetickets.com, sebastienpresents.com, or
eventvibe.com. Call 415.979.3031 for more information. 21+ information:
eventvibe.com, sebastienpresents.com, or groovetickets.com

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D239 San

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Soulive **

Mystery Machine Productions presents...Soulive Plus DJ Logic and Lettuce

Soulive is a band whose time has come. This groovy combo are trailblazers
in defining a new branch of the Hip-Hop tree. Their flawless sound fluidly
combines the soul and jazz of the past with the inventive sound of today's
hip-hop, dub, funk, and dance music. As a result, this New York City trio
is a melting pot of jazzy harmonies, soul drenched ballads, hip-hop
rhythms, and no-nonsense funk. But it is Soulive's raucous live
performances that have earned them a devoted legion of fans few of their
contemporaries can brag about. They have sold out clubs across the nation
and show no signs of letting up soon. $100 includes open bar, 21+. Located
@DNA Lounge, 375 11th Street (11th @ Harrison), San Francisco, Soma

Tuesday, December 31, 2002 ** Submerge **

Submerge Rain Dance invites you PROCEEDS BENEFIT THE 418 PROJECT 418 Front
St. Santa Cruz New Years Eve 9pm - 6 am 2002-2003 Djs Tipper (U.K.Nu
School Breaks Pioneer )UK- Fuel, Sony, Myutopia- "SURROUNDED"  Album
Release Tour.

Part of the late-'90s drum'n'bass subgenre nu breaks, British
DJ/artist/producer/car aficionado Tipper became entranced by the style at
age 16, when his older brother turned him on to the whole rave culture.
Eventually growing bored with the fast tempos and repetitiveness of
drum'n'bass, Tipper began to experiment with new tempos leading to his
debut album, The Critical Path, in 2000 on the Higher Ground/Sony label.
During the making of the album, Tipper began to suffer from hearing damage
due to the elaborate and booming stereo systems inside his cars. With the
problem sorted out, Tipper returned a year later with his sophomore effort
(and first for the Pandisc label), Tipper Presents Sound Off, which
eventually led to tours of both Europe and America.Tracy Little John Rob
Monroy Stridah N-Man Alia Adam Rodman Kikkoman Tom L-G Cool Hand Luke,
Midnight Countdown ceremony. Sound by Magnetic Organic Treats from
Convergence, Ritual Fire Dance and Drumming. Heated outdoor Lounge. The
418 Project is a non-profit venue run by and for all forms of the Santa
Cruz dance community Please Show Your Support $12 pre@Streetlight 939
Pacific ave. $15door/Doors open 9pm/All ages Happy New Year!

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D387

Thursday, January 2, 2003 ** Weekly: Popscene **

Every Thursday evening, Mod Lang Records present...Popscene! Featuring
Britpop, mod, 60s soul, new wave, indie and electronica grooves With DJs
Aaron & Jeremy. Every Thursday Evening.

Jeremy P. Goldstein, popscene co-founder and DJ, is "excited to see the
club's popularity remain so vibrant for 5 years now. I cherish the
opportunity to share the music that is so important to me with an equally
passionate fanbase. Our crowd is really knowledgeable and we love to hear
their suggestions." Aaron Axelsen, fellow popscene co- founder and DJ
agrees. "It's been so rewarding to present this club for 5 years in a city
like San Francisco, with its rich and varied musical history, a city that
embraces diversity; a city that allows us to throw a night where our
supporters dance to a eclectic mix of music from Pulp to The Rolling
Stones to the Chemical Brothers to The Jackson 5."

Presented by the SF Weekly, popscene hosts the hottest and most unique
weekly nightclub every Thursday 10 pm - 3 am at 330 Ritch Street, where
ages 18 and over groove to the tunes of Britpop, indie, mod, new wave,
electronic and '60s soul. Popscene features dancing, cocktails, live bands
and record release parties.

18+ information: 415.263.0365, or www.popscene-sf.com

Thursday, January 2, 2003 ** Weekly: Kit Kat **

(Every Thursday Night) - Kit Kat introduced the weekly party concept to
San Francisco in March 1989 and against all odds established itself as the
only Thursday night party worthy of a monster sweat. Today Kit Kat sits on
a Richter proof funk foundation which is shaken to the core by local
fanatics determined to dance their ass off. This party has inexplicably
managed to elude the weekend warrior virus and has a balls to the wall
energy behind it. By default The End Up provides a comfortable who cares
what you are wearing atmosphere, so all attitude inevitably gets checked
at the door. The party gets started right away and peaks when the local
after hour posse swings on to the dance floor and pushes the elevator
above cloud line in the nick of closing time.

The knobs are manhandled by resident DJ Marc Jellybear whom in turn passes
the closing baton to rotating guests Simon, Garth, Miguel Migs, Jonene,
Wyatt Earp & John Howard. In addition the club hosts monthly special
events with the next level of over hyped DJs that have been, however,
thoroughly Kit Kat tested and do in the end justify having to pass the hat
around for business class airfare.

Overall a guaranteed must call in sick in the next few hours experience.
To join the guest list & receive passes via e-mail:
kitkatVIP@sbcglobal.net

time: 10:30 pm - 4:30 am Free before 11 pm, $12 cover after, 21+ Located @
The End Up, 401 Sixth St., Corner of 6th and Harrison Streets, San
Francisco - SOMA

http://www.hyperreal.org:8080/raves/sf/events/view?identifier=3D289 San
Francisco California, USA

Friday, January 10, 2003 ** Monthly: Heroine **

Heroine Please join us the second Friday night of the month at Sno-Drift
for our next dose of Heroine, an all-female DJ line-up. The term heroine
was originally brought to India by Alexander The Great. The Ancient Greeks
used the word to describe those goddesses who descended from the heavens
to vanquish evil wherever it was present in the mortal realm. These
heroines are still amongst us... We welcome the following goddesses to the
turntables: DJ Alicia (LA), Scarlett Etienne (NYC), Kimmy, Tina, Daniela,
and Pam the Funktress. The buzz around this one keeps getting louder and
it looks like this party will be THE party of the night in the Bay Area.
We look forward to seeing each of you the second Friday night of the month
at Sno-Drift for our next dose of Heroine. For booth reservation info
(there are only 4 booths still available!): please email

 Liquid Latex present Nectar.

Deep within a beautiful, exotic flower is a small, sweet, ambrosial
center. Rowena of Risque and Yana of Walking Art would like to introduce
Nectar; a select, fashionable and attractive crowd, in an exquisite,
sensual atmosphere, surrounded by deep, seductive house beats. You are
invited to revel in an atmosphere steeped in sensuality. You are invited
to lose yourself to engaging house music or just sit back and watch. You
are invited to be hypnotized by sultry and seductive models displaying
unique liquid latex designs.We have been meeting a lot of wonderful new
people and would like to introduce our old friends to our new friends, and
make Nectar the night for people to mingle, dance and enjoy themselves.

A note to our new guests: This is a woman-centric event being hosted by
two women. It is a place where women and couples can go and dance the
night away, chill with friends, or explore an inner sensual side. To keep
this atmosphere relaxed, fun and well-balanced we ask that each gentleman
attending Nectar come escorted by a lady. This is not a swingers club.

-------------------------------------------------------
     SFRaves.org Calendar Administrative Notes
-------------------------------------------------------

SFRaves.org serves the greater SF Bay Area, but reaches beyond the local
scene to all corners of the Terra Firma. Thanks to those of SFRAVES.org
community, whose support and network have been a honour to serve.

Please notify me regarding new events, event changes, deprecated event
information, or any other information pertaining to events in the greater
SF Bay Area and beyond. The SFR Calendar is sent via email every week.

Please contact me @ karina@hyperreal.org

To subscribe to the list, send a message to:
sfraves-calendar-subscribe@hyperreal.org

To remove your address from the list, send a message to:
sfraves-calendar-unsubscribe@hyperreal.org

Send mail to the following for info and FAQ for this list:
sfraves-calendar-info@hyperreal.org or sfraves-calendar-faq@hyperreal.org

Faithfully yours, -- Karina Powers karina@hyperreal.org

Copyright: All trademarks, product or service names, brand names and/or
logos appearing on http://www.sfraves.org site, calendar and archives are
the property of their respective owners.

For additional commands, e-mail: sfraves-help@hyperreal.org

SFRaves.com Belongs to Vorg Entertainment. Long ago, they promised to turn
the domain over to Brian B, but they decided that making money would be a
better idea. So, there are two different sites... Sfraves.org is
non-profit, and Sfraves.com is for-profit (via overpriced tshirts &
accessories and banner advertisements).

Have a great new years everyone!

John Vicondoa
johnv@hyperreal.org
